# Return Code Error Handling

## Requirement

All functions that can fail SHALL return an integer status code.

Return value of 0 SHALL indicate success.

Return value of a negative number SHALL indicate an error condition.

Error codes SHALL be defined consistently, either as macros or enum values, with descriptive names.

Error codes SHALL be documented in function documentation.

Callers SHALL check return values from functions that can fail.

Error conditions SHALL be propagated to callers unless they can be handled locally.

When a function encounters an error, it SHALL clean up any resources it has allocated before returning.

